63,Who were Wang Jiawei and Nyima Gyaincain?,The exact nature of relations between Tibet and the Ming dynasty of China (1368\u20131644) is unclear
63,Who were Wang Jiawei and Nyima Gyaincain?, Analysis of the relationship is further complicated by modern political conflicts and the application of Westphalian sovereignty to a time when the concept did not exist
63,Who were Wang Jiawei and Nyima Gyaincain?, Some Mainland Chinese scholars, such as Wang Jiawei and Nyima Gyaincain, assert that the Ming dynasty had unquestioned sovereignty over Tibet, pointing to the Ming court's issuing of various titles to Tibetan leaders, Tibetans' full acceptance of these titles, and a renewal process for successors of these titles that involved traveling to the Ming capital
63,Who were Wang Jiawei and Nyima Gyaincain?, Scholars within China also argue that Tibet has been an integral part of China since the 13th century and that it was thus a part of the Ming Empire
63,Who were Wang Jiawei and Nyima Gyaincain?, But most scholars outside China, such as Turrell V
63,Who were Wang Jiawei and Nyima Gyaincain?, Wylie, Melvin C
63,Who were Wang Jiawei and Nyima Gyaincain?, Goldstein, and Helmut Hoffman, say that the relationship was one of suzerainty, that Ming titles were only nominal, that Tibet remained an independent region outside Ming control, and that it simply paid tribute until the Jiajing Emperor (1521\u20131566), who ceased relations with Tibet

218,What are some other names the Dutch Republic is known by?,The Dutch Republic, also known as the Republic of the Seven United Netherlands (Republiek der Zeven Verenigde Nederlanden), Republic of the United Netherlands or Republic of the Seven United Provinces (Republiek der Zeven Verenigde Provinci\u00ebn), was a republic in Europe existing from 1581, when part of the Netherlands separated from Spanish rule, until 1795

857,What is the first step in the human digestive system?,In the human digestive system, food enters the mouth and mechanical digestion of the food starts by the action of mastication (chewing), a form of mechanical digestion, and the wetting contact of saliva
857,What is the first step in the human digestive system?, Saliva, a liquid secreted by the salivary glands, contains salivary amylase, an enzyme which starts the digestion of starch in the food; the saliva also contains mucus, which lubricates the food, and hydrogen carbonate, which provides the ideal conditions of pH (alkaline) for amylase to work
857,What is the first step in the human digestive system?, After undergoing mastication and starch digestion, the food will be in the form of a small, round slurry mass called a bolus
857,What is the first step in the human digestive system?, It will then travel down the esophagus and into the stomach by the action of peristalsis
857,What is the first step in the human digestive system?, Gastric juice in the stomach starts protein digestion
857,What is the first step in the human digestive system?, Gastric juice mainly contains hydrochloric acid and pepsin
857,What is the first step in the human digestive system?, As these two chemicals may damage the stomach wall, mucus is secreted by the stomach, providing a slimy layer that acts as a shield against the damaging effects of the chemicals
857,What is the first step in the human digestive system?, At the same time protein digestion is occurring, mechanical mixing occurs by peristalsis, which is waves of muscular contractions that move along the stomach wall
857,What is the first step in the human digestive system?, This allows the mass of food to further mix with the digestive enzymes

914,When was John born?,John was born to Henry II of England and Eleanor of Aquitaine on 24 December 1166
914,When was John born?, Henry had inherited significant territories along the Atlantic seaboard\u2014Anjou, Normandy and England\u2014and expanded his empire by conquering Brittany
914,When was John born?, Henry married the powerful Eleanor of Aquitaine, who reigned over the Duchy of Aquitaine and had a tenuous claim to Toulouse and Auvergne in southern France, in addition to being the former wife of Louis VII of France
914,When was John born?, The result was the Angevin Empire, named after Henry's paternal title as Count of Anjou and, more specifically, its seat in Angers
914,When was John born?,[nb 2] The Empire, however, was inherently fragile: although all the lands owed allegiance to Henry, the disparate parts each had their own histories, traditions and governance structures
914,When was John born?, As one moved south through Anjou and Aquitaine, the extent of Henry's power in the provinces diminished considerably, scarcely resembling the modern concept of an empire at all
914,When was John born?, Some of the traditional ties between parts of the empire such as Normandy and England were slowly dissolving over time
914,When was John born?, It was unclear what would happen to the empire on Henry's death
914,When was John born?, Although the custom of primogeniture, under which an eldest son would inherit all his father's lands, was slowly becoming more widespread across Europe, it was less popular amongst the Norman kings of England
914,When was John born?, Most believed that Henry would divide the empire, giving each son a substantial portion, and hoping that his children would continue to work together as allies after his death
914,When was John born?, To complicate matters, much of the Angevin empire was held by Henry only as a vassal of the King of France of the rival line of the House of Capet
914,When was John born?, Henry had often allied himself with the Holy Roman Emperor against France, making the feudal relationship even more challenging

1557,What two key elements that distinguish literature as a written form of art?,Literature consists of written productions, often restricted to those deemed to have artistic or intellectual value
1557,What two key elements that distinguish literature as a written form of art?, Its Latin root literatura/litteratura (derived itself from littera, letter or handwriting) was used to refer to all written accounts, but intertwined with the roman concept of cultura: learning or cultivation
1557,What two key elements that distinguish literature as a written form of art?, Literature often uses language differently than ordinary language (see literariness)
1557,What two key elements that distinguish literature as a written form of art?, Literature can be classified according to whether it is fiction or non-fiction and whether it is poetry or prose; it can be further distinguished according to major forms such as the novel, short story or drama; and works are often categorised according to historical periods or their adherence to certain aesthetic features or expectations (genre)

1558,What are two major divisions of literature?, Literature can be classified according to whether it is fiction or non-fiction and whether it is poetry or prose; it can be further distinguished according to major forms such as the novel, short story or drama; and works are often categorised according to historical periods or their adherence to certain aesthetic features or expectations (genre)

1559,Besides this major division, what are two other sub-divisions to describe literature?, Its Latin root literatura/litteratura (derived itself from littera, letter or handwriting) was used to refer to all written accounts, but intertwined with the roman concept of cultura: learning or cultivation
1559,Besides this major division, what are two other sub-divisions to describe literature?, Literature often uses language differently than ordinary language (see literariness)

1811,What is the third hottest desert in the world?,The Sahara (Arabic: \u0627\u0644\u0635\u062d\u0631\u0627\u0621 \u0627\u0644\u0643\u0628\u0631\u0649\u200e, a\u1e63-\u1e63a\u1e25r\u0101\u02be al-kubr\u0101\u202f, 'the Greatest Desert') is the largest hot desert in the world

1811,What is the third hottest desert in the world?, The desert comprises much of the land found within North Africa, excluding the fertile coastal region situated against the Mediterranean Sea, the Atlas Mountains of the Maghreb, and the Nile Valley of Egypt and Sudan

2307,What does DBMS stand for?,A database management system (DBMS) is a computer software application that interacts with the user, other applications, and the database itself to capture and analyze data
2307,What does DBMS stand for?, A general-purpose DBMS is designed to allow the definition, creation, querying, update, and administration of databases
2307,What does DBMS stand for?, Well-known DBMSs include MySQL, PostgreSQL, Microsoft SQL Server, Oracle, Sybase, SAP HANA, and IBM DB2
2307,What does DBMS stand for?, A database is not generally portable across different DBMSs, but different DBMS can interoperate by using standards such as SQL and ODBC or JDBC to allow a single application to work with more than one DBMS
2307,What does DBMS stand for?, Database management systems are often classified according to the database model that they support; the most popular database systems since the 1980s have all supported the relational model as represented by the SQL language

2330,What is the relationships between plants animals and bacteria?, Bacteria inhabit soil, water, acidic hot springs, radioactive waste, and the deep portions of Earth's crust
2330,What is the relationships between plants animals and bacteria?, Bacteria also live in symbiotic and parasitic relationships with plants and animals
2330,What is the relationships between plants animals and bacteria?, They are also known to have flourished in manned spacecraft
